\int_{0}^{2\pi}\int_{0}^{d}\exp\!\Big(\frac{-r^2 +2\alpha\; r\cos\theta}{4\;\sigma^2}\Big)r\; dr\; d\theta
   \int_0^{2 \pi} \exp\left( \frac{ \alpha r}{2 \sigma^2} \cos \theta \right) \, \mathrm{d} \theta = 2 \pi I_0 \left( \frac{ \alpha r}{2 \sigma^2} \right) 
   \lim_{d \to \infty} \mathcal{I}_d = 4 \pi \sigma^2 \exp\left( \frac{\alpha^2}{4 \sigma^2} \right) 
